OL,3,CMan threatened to kill neighbour due
OL,4,Cto her dogs barking
OL,6,FMs Egan said: "He kept getting in her
OL,7,Fface. The defendant grabbed her and
OL,8,Fthrew her to the floor. The
OL,9,Fcomplainant said that when she landed,
OL,10,Fshe was in intense pain and began
OL,11,Fscreaming.
OL,13,F"She believed the defendant was under
OL,14,Fthe influence of something due to his
OL,15,Fmanner."
OL,17,FA taxi was called, and Ms Davies'
OL,18,Fneighbour managed to get Lane into it.
OL,19,FHe was arrested the next day. He later
OL,20,Fpleaded guilty to assault causing
OL,21,Factual bodily harm.
